Cognitive Systems Research is a scientific journal that covers all topics in the study of cognitive science, both natural and artificial cognitive systems. It is published by Elsevier. The journal publishes 4 issues a year and is abstracted and indexed in Scopus and the Science Citation Index. According to the Journal Citation Reports, its 2008 impact factor is 1.581. The editors in chief are R. Sun of Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute and V.G. Honavar or Iowa State University, Ames.
